L0000: db '"'Tis as I suspected. Bollux thought he must sacrifice his o'
 db 'wn heart to return my life."~If you were to believe it possi'
 db 'ble, you would feel positive you had just seen a drop of wat'
 db 'er fall from the golem's right eye.~"The poor fool gave his '
 db 'life for mine. I can only hope I would have done the same.~"'
 db 'Doing so now, however, would help nothing, for once I was go'
 db 'ne Bollux would simply repeat his act." You hear a sigh come'
 db ' from the golem.'
L01B4: db 00
L01B5: db 'I don't mean to be irreverent, but did the matter not involv'
 db 'e death, 'twould be a humorous sight: the two golems popping'
 db ' up and down as each one passed the `heart' to the other...@'
L0269: db 00
L026A: db '"However," smiles Adjhar, "'tis not necessary, for had Bollu'
 db 'x known what is covered by this smudge, he could have told t'
 db 'hee that a new heart may be cut from the Tree of Life. Look '
 db 'here," he says, pointing to a line in the tome smeared with '
 db 'dried mud. "I remember this from before. Thou canst take the'
 db ' very same pick with which thou didst collect the blood and '
 db 'procure a `heart' for Bollux. Of course, after thou dost pla'
 db 'ce the heart upon Bollux's body, thou must again perform the'
 db ' same ritual of blood."'
